<dashboard version="1.1" theme="dark">
  <label>T1219 — Remote Access Software (RMM)</label>
  <description>DNS-driven IOC detection for RMM-tool abuse (TeamViewer, AnyDesk, ScreenConnect). Lookup-driven; populate rmm_user_allowlist.csv to suppress sanctioned use.</description>

  <fieldset submitButton="false" autoRun="true">
    <input type="time" token="time">
      <label>Time range</label>
      <default>
        <earliest>-24h@h</earliest>
        <latest>now</latest>
      </default>
    </input>
    <input type="text" token="src_filter" searchWhenChanged="true">
      <label>Source IP</label>
      <default>*</default>
    </input>
  </fieldset>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Suspect sources</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>`rmm_tool_use`
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| stats dc(src)</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="colorBy">value</option>
        <option name="rangeValues">[0,1,5]</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0x53a051","0xf8be34","0xdc4e41"]</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <title>RMM tools observed</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>`rmm_tool_use`
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| stats dc(tools)</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <title>Lookup size (RMM domains)</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>| inputlookup rmm_domains.csv | stats count</query>
        </search>
      </single>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Suspect (window, src) groups</title>
      <table>
        <search>
          <query>`rmm_tool_use`
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| eval window=strftime(_time, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")
| sort -distinct_rmm_domains
| table window, src, distinct_rmm_domains, total_queries, tools, sample_domains</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="count">25</option>
      </table>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Resolution volume by RMM tool</title>
      <chart>
        <search>
          <query>`rmm_tool_use`
| stats count BY tools
| sort -count</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="charting.chart">bar</option>
      </chart>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>About this detection</title>
      <html>
        <h3>T1219 — Remote Access Software</h3>
        <p>
          Modern ransomware crews avoid bespoke implants and instead abuse
          legitimate Remote Monitoring &amp; Management SaaS — TeamViewer,
          AnyDesk, ScreenConnect, ConnectWise. The DFIR Report and CISA
          have catalogued this technique extensively in 2023–2025
          ransomware engagements.
        </p>
        <p>
          The detection enriches dns.log with the
          <code>rmm_domains.csv</code> lookup and flags any source that
          resolves an RMM-tool domain in a 5-min window. Use
          <code>rmm_user_allowlist.csv</code> to suppress sanctioned
          help-desk / MSP-managed endpoints.
        </p>
        <p>
          Tuning + false-positive notes:
          <a href="https://github.com/JacobRHess/detlab/blob/main/cases/t1219_rmm_tool_use/README.md" target="_blank">cases/t1219_rmm_tool_use/README.md</a>
        </p>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>
</dashboard>
